counts...\n\nNow I'm tracing through what happens when ClickHouse returns a single row with level 0 and count 500 — the levelCounts map gets populated, but then when computing userCounts, the inner loop never executes because Math.min(0, steps.length) equals 0, leaving all step counts at zero. That's actually the right behavior if nobody reached step 1, but I'm realizing the test case for empty results might be checking something different — whether we should return an empty steps array when the table itself has no rows versus when users simply didn't progress through the funnel.\n\nLooking at the spec, it shows steps in the array even with zero users, which suggests the current implementation returning `{ steps: [] }` for completely empty results might be a deviation, though the spec doesn't explicitly address this edge case.\n\nFor the integration test, I'll focus on validating that a successful POST returns the correct structure with seeded data, checking that validation errors are caught at the HTTP level, and confirming the response shape matches the spec.\n\nWriting the integration test...","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":2992,"cache_read_input_tokens":47408,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":2992},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"39cbed89-9497-4111-903f-16ff18e0c764","uuid":"5a7676a7-fcce-4357-84df-f4371496bf2c"}
